## Analysis

**Root Cause:** The RPM package check found an unpackaged directory `/usr/lib/python3.13/site-packages/oterm`. This happened because the `%files` section is missing the main Python site-packages entry (`%{python_sitelib}/%name`). Without this line, all files under that directory are considered "unpacked" and cause a build failure.

**Fix:** Add `/%{python_sitelib}/%name` to the `%files` section alongside the dist-info entry. The correct `%files` block should include:
- `/usr/bin/oterm` (binary)
- `/%{python_sitelib}/%name` (package files)
- `/%{python_sitelib}/%name-%version.dist-info` (metadata)

**BuildRequires:** The build completed successfully, so no missing BuildRequires were detected. The `%pyproject_wheel` and `%pyproject_install` macros automatically handle Python dependencies.